{{Infobox Figure Skating Competition | title= 1984 Prize of Moscow News | imagesize= | caption= | comptype= | startdate= December 5 | enddate= 9 | skatingseason= 1984-85 | location= [[Moscow]] | host= | venue= | prizemoney= | championmen= {{flagathlete|[[Alexandre Fadeev]]|URS}} | championladies= {{flagathlete| [[Kira Ivanova]]|URS}} | championpairs= {{flagathlete|[[Larisa Selezneva]] / [[Oleg Makarov (figure skater)|Oleg Makarov]]|URS}} | championdance= {{flagathlete|[[Marina Klimova]] / [[Sergei Ponomarenko]]|URS}} | previouscomp= [[1983 Prize of Moscow News]] | nextcomp= [[1985 Prize of Moscow News]] | previousgp= | nextgp= }}
The '''1984 [[Prize of Moscow News]]''' was the 19th edition of an international figure skating competition organized in [[Moscow]], [[Soviet Union]]. It was held December 5–9, 1984. Medals were awarded in the disciplines of [[single skating|men's singles, ladies' singles]], [[pair skating]] and [[ice dancing]]. The men's category was won by European champion [[Alexandre Fadeev]], who would end his season with the world title. The ladies' gold medal went to Olympic medalist [[Kira Ivanova]], winning her fourth Prize of Moscow News title. Olympic medalists [[Larisa Selezneva]] / [[Oleg Makarov (figure skater)|Oleg Makarov]] took the pairs' title, earning their second win at the Prize of Moscow News. In the ice dancing category, Olympic bronze medalists [[Marina Klimova]] / [[Sergei Ponomarenko]] defeated the Olympic silver medalists [[Natalia Bestemianova]] / [[Andrei Bukin]].
