{{Politics of Algeria}}
'''Elections to the Algerian Assembly''' were held in Algeria in February 1951.<ref name=DS>[[Dolf Sternberger]], [[Bernhard Vogel (politician)|Bernhard Vogel]], [[Dieter Nohlen]] & Klaus Landfried (1978) ''Die Wahl der Parlamente: Band II: Afrika, Erster Halbband'', p432 {{de icon}}</ref> Like other post-1948 elections in French Algeria, it was rigged by the authorities to ensure the defeat of Algerian nationalists.<ref name=FT>Frank Tachau (1994) ''Political parties of the Middle East and North Africa'', Greenwood Press, p10</ref>
==Electoral system== The Assembly was elected by two colleges, each of which elected 60 seats; the First College consisted of Europeans and [[évolué]]s, whilst the Second College was composed of the remainder of the Algerian population.
