ocrinologist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate * 1924 &ndash; [[Sam B. Hall, Jr.]], American lawyer, judge, and politician (d. 1994) * 1924 &ndash; [[Slim Harpo]], American blues singer-songwriter and musician (d. 1970) *[[1925]] &ndash; [[Grant Tinker]], American television producer, co-founded [[MTM Enterprises]] (d. 2016) *[[1926]] &ndash; [[Lev Dyomin]], Russian colonel, pilot, and astronaut (d. 1998) *[[1928]] &ndash; [[Alan Bowness]], English historian and curator * 1928 &ndash; [[David L. Wolper]], American director and producer (d. 2010) *[[1929]] &ndash; [[Dmitri Bruns]], Estonian architect and theorist *[[1930]] &ndash; [[Ron Mulock]], Australian lawyer and politician, 10th [[Deputy Premier of New South Wales]] (d. 2014) * 1930 &ndash; [[Rod Taylor]], Australian-American actor and screenwriter (d. 2015) *[[1931]] &ndash; [[Betty Churcher]], Australian painter, historian, and curator (d. 2015) * 1931 &ndash; [[Mary Rodgers]], American composer and author (d. 2014) *[[1932]] &ndash; [[Alfonso Arau]], Mexican actor and director *[[1933]] &ndash; [[Goldie Hill]], American country singer-songwriter and guitarist (d. 2005) *[[1934]] &ndash; [[Jean Chrétien]], Canadian lawyer and politician, 20th [[Prime Minister of Canada]] *[[1936]] &ndash; [[Eva Hesse]], German-American sculptor and educator (d. 1970) *[[1938]] &ndash; [[Arthur Scargill]], English miner, activist, and politician *[[1939]] &ndash; [[Anne Heggtveit]], Canadian alpine skier *[[1940]] &ndash; [[Andres Tarand]], Estonian geographer and politician, 10th [[Prime Minister of Estonia]] *[[1941]] &ndash; [[Gérson]], Brazilian footballer *[[1942]] &ndash; [[Bud Acton]], American basketball player * 1942 &ndash; [[Clarence Clemons]], American saxophonist and actor (d. 2011) * 1942 &ndash; [[Leo Cullum]], American soldier, pilot, and cartoonist (d. 2010) * 1942 &ndash; [[George Mira]], American football player *[[1943]] &ndash; [[Jim Hightower]], American journalist and politi