Midburn ([[Hebrew language|Hebrew]]: מידברן; [[Arabic language|Arabic]]: ميدبيرن) is a 6-day event held in the [[Negev|Negev Desert]] in southern [[Israel]].<ref>{{Citation | title = Inside Midburn, Israel’s version of Burning Man | url = http://america.aljazeera.com/multimedia/photo-gallery/2014/6/photos-inside-israelsownburningmanfestival.html | author = | journal = [[Al Jazeera]] | date = 9 June 2014 | accessdate = 16 June 2014}}</ref> The first annual event was held in June, 2014, and was attended by 3,000 people.<ref>{{Citation | title = Midburn in Israel’s Negev desert was a bizarre first attempt at the popular US festival Burning Man | url = http://www.news.com.au/travel/world-travel/midburn-in-israels-negev-desert-was-a-bizarre-first-attempt-at-the-popular-us-festival-burning-man/story-e6frfqc0-1226950365238 | author = | journal = [[News.com.au]] | date = 11 June 2014 | accessdate = 16 June 2014}}</ref> The second event was held in May 20-24, 2015, and was attended by 6,500 people. The name itself is a [[portmanteau]] of the Hebrew word for "desert" (מידבר ''midbar'') and the English word "burn" in reference to the annual [[Burning Man]] festival in the [[Nevada desert]]. <ref>{{Citation | title = Now You Can Go to Burning Man After Birthright | url = http://time.com/2848120/israel-burning-man/ | author = | journal = [[Time (magazine)|TIME]] | date = 9 June 2014 | accessdate = 16 June 2014}}</ref> 

The festival is held near [[Sde Boker]],<ref>{{Citation | title = Israele: il Midburn festival, il deserto diventa "creativo" | url = http://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2014/06/09/foto/midburn_festival_follie_e_condivisione_nel_deserto_israeliano-88484567/ | author = | journal = [[la Repubblica]] | language = Italian | date = 11 June 2014 | accessdate = 16 June 2014}}</ref> and the themes of the event are creativity, art and personal expression.<ref>{{Citation | title = Midburn : festival déjanté en plein désert d'Israël | url = http://tempsreel.nouvelobs.com/galeries-photos/photo/20140610.OBS0008/photos-midburn-festival-dejante-en-plein-desert-d-israel.html | author =  Cyril Bonnet | journal = [[Le Nouvel Observateur]] | language = French | date = 10 June 2014 | accessdate = 16 June 2014}}</ref> 

The burn is held every year in May or June, around the Hebrew holiday of "[[Shavuot]]" (Pentecost), and culminates in a bonfire of wooden sculptures.  The third Midburn event, in 2016, had an attendance of 8,000 participants, making it the 2nd biggest regional event outside the US, after [[AfrikaBurn]]. As of 2018, it is the only Burning Man regional event in the [[Middle East]].

